Miranda Devine has apologised after calling David Pocock a 'tosser' for celebrating a try using sign language . 
  Pocock scored a hat-trick of tries for Australian Super Rugby team the Brumbies on Friday night . 
  Devine had assumed Pocock was doing 'jazz hands' but he was actually doing sign language for a friend . 
  She tweeted: 'Did Pocock actually do jazz hands when he celebrated a try?!!! What a tosser!'